'''聯邦鐵路管理局'''（{{lang-en|Federal Railroad Administration}}，簡稱'''FRA'''）是[[美國運輸部|美國運輸部]]轄下的機構之一，乃依《1966年運輸部法》（{{lang-en|Department of Transportation Act of 1966}}）成立<ref>United States. ''Department of Transportation Act.'' {{usc|49|103}}, section 3(e)(1).</ref>，主要目的為頒布並執行[[鐵路運輸|鐵路]]安全[[行政法規|行政法規]]、管理鐵路援助方案、進行研究和開發以支持改進鐵路安全和國家鐵路運輸政策、重整[[東北走廊|東北走廊]]鐵路客運服務，以及凝聚政府對於鐵路運輸活動的支持。<ref>Federal Railroad Administration (FRA). [http://www.fra.dot.gov/us/content/2 "Federal Railroad Administration: About Us."] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080519000832/http://www.fra.dot.gov/us/content/2 |date=2008-05-19 }}</ref>

FRA是運輸部十個聯運（各種交通方式混合運作）機構的其中之一。該機構在其局長及副局長辦公室之下設有七個分支單位：財務管理部門、首席法律顧問、公民權利部門、公共事務部門、公眾參與部門、鐵路政策與發展部門、安全部門。<ref>Federal Railroad Administration (2010). Washington, DC.[http://www.fra.dot.gov/Pages/2.shtml "About the FRA."] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100914000636/http://www.fra.dot.gov/Pages/2.shtml |date=2010-09-14 }} Accessed 2010-08-28.</ref>

== 安全措施 ==
2015年6月，FRA宣布[[Google|Google]]將運用其[[GIS|GIS]]數據於該公司之地圖服務中；該數據資料可以精確定位美國境內250,000餘處[[平交道|平交道]]。FRA相信提供該數據可以提升導航系統使用者駛經平交道時之安全性。<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.transportation.gov/fastlane/fra-google-team-to-incorporate-rail-data-in-maps|title=Google, FRA team up for safety; will add rail crossing data to maps|date=June 29, 2015|accessdate=April 27, 2016|archive-date=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219162641/https://www.transportation.gov/fastlane/fra-google-team-to-incorporate-rail-data-in-maps|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{citenews|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/29/technology/agency-taps-mapping-technology-to-curb-rail-crossing-accidents.html?_r=0|title=Agency Taps Mapping Technology to Curb Rail Crossing Accidents|first=Jad|last=Mouawad|date=June 29, 2015|newspaper=New York Times|accessdate=April 27, 2016|archive-date=2017-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128225836/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/29/technology/agency-taps-mapping-technology-to-curb-rail-crossing-accidents.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

